SOMEONE IS HERE. I CAN FEEL IT.
I CANT ESCAPE ITS TOO LATE
SO THIS IS WHERE I DIE...
ONE. TWO. THREE. THEY WILL COME FOR ME
I KNOW YOU ARE THERE. SHOW YOURSELF!

item.strainsofascension.guidebook_layers:
§k1234567890abcdefghijklmnopqrstuv§r

§n§lChapter 6:§r§r
Layers of the Abyss

  It is said that one, the abyss was a local phenomena. However for unknown reason, the effects of the abyss have now spread everywhere. Though, the under-

ground is riddled with countless sources of dangers, there are some that are more dangerous then all of them. These dangers are the strains. One who enters the underground is certain to encounter the strains of the abyss.

The abyss can be divided into 9 known layers, all of which have a specific strain. Not only are the strains in the deeper layers more severe to the health of a delver, they also stack down. Meaning one who is effected by the strains of the 3rd layer will also receive the strains of

the first and second layer. This makes it extremely dangerous to go to the lower layers, as returning will put an immense strain on the delvers body and mind. In the following chapters, the layers and their strains will be described in further detail.

§nDelvers are advised to not go beyond the third layer for their own safety.§r

Only elite delvers are allowed to venture in to the depth below the third layer and only a handful have ever set foot in the 7th layer. Though, the 8th layer has been successfully entered,

it would be certain death for the average human. There is one documented journey attempting to go beyond the 8th layer and into the 9th. While none of the delvers in the expedition survived the journey, the existence of the 9th layer has been confirmed by a letter
which was pulled up using a rope. §k1234
